                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="commtext c00">As an aside, when people point out virtue signalling (I&#x27;m taking it as an analogue of status games) without adding some analysis my first assumption is that they are virtue-signalling to put others down or make others seem shallow (or themselves deep). The cornerstone of western morality is Jesus and he was quite the &quot;virtue signaller&quot;. Point being that the observation on it&#x27;s own is uninteresting without saying something about the context or consequences of a behaviour. There aren&#x27;t many things that are &#x2F;purely&#x2F; virtue signals (or status games) and those that are, are quite obvious.</span>
