                  <span class="commtext c00">Jesus spoke about humility and dying for your beliefs, which he did. Martyrs don&#x27;t need to signal their virtue (or social status), they do the virtous thing.<p>Status is a public display of desireability. It doesn&#x27;t have much to do with virtue, but everyone wants it anyway.<p>Don&#x27;t blend those two concepts, they are separate. People who make a public display and performance out of their virtues, &#x27;virtue signallers&#x27; miss the point. You do it in humility before God.<p>People who don&#x27;t show off their status, get little benefit out of it.</span>
