                  <span class="commtext c00">Recently I got the game &quot;The Logical Journey of the Zoombinis&quot; for my kids to play on steam since I got young kids and I remember loving that game when I was younger.<p>The game is amazing, the way it combines fun, learning, and engaging kids without ever feeling like it&#x27;s a lesson. Seriously my 5 year old now has a basic understanding of set theory because of it.<p>It feels like educational games peaked in the late 90&#x27;s and early 2000&#x27;s and everything since then has been a regression that spends too much time trying to explain things to students rather than letting them discover and explore for themselves.</span>
