                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="commtext c00">Railroads.  Specifically freight rail.<p>There is stunningly little literature on any R&amp;D in conventional freight rail transport, something I discovered when looking for any published research some months back.<p>High-speed rail, yes.  Regular old freight, no.<p>Contrast this with autonomous and electrified trucking as alternatives, with which rail could offer considerable synergies.<p>I&#x27;d suspect that break-bulk, trainset assembly and disassembly, and routing might all offer opportunities.<p>But ... nada.<p>I suspect other modalities within the transport sector might be similar, notably ocean shipping.</span>
