                  <span class="commtext c00">Average net profit is very low ($10K) but it&#x27;s because majority of farmers are old small family, They also receive pension, may work on another part time job, eat their own veges, and do barter exchange. Average net profit for full-timer (under 65yo) is also lower ($30K) but to be fair local jobs salary is also tend to low,<p>Here, problem is that there are few newcomer to be a farmer. It&#x27;s unpopular to live rural area. People in rural area are generally considered to treat newcomers unkindly. Local people grown by farmer also don&#x27;t want to choose farming as a first career (but may choose after retiring, or help father&#x27;s farming). Farming lands have been tend to be divided for small lands (partially thanks to WW2 lose), and generally Japan lands aren&#x27;t so flat, so productivity isn&#x27;t great thus income isn&#x27;t great.</span>
