                <tr class='athing comtr' id='32627500'><td><table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind' indent='3'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="120"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks">
      <center><a id='up_32627500'href='vote?id=32627500&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D32611247'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center>    </td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=7952" class="hnuser">7952</a> <span class="age" title="2022-08-28T11:26:15"><a href="item?id=32627500">40 days ago</a></span> <span id="unv_32627500"></span>          <span class='navs'>
             | <a href="#32611951" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">root</a> | <a href="#32612828" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">parent</a> | <a href="#32612056" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">next</a> <a class="togg clicky" id="32627500" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)">[–]</a><span class="onstory"></span>          </span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="commtext c00">I work in an infrastructure field with lots of engineering disciplines doing separate design.  Designs are typically exchanged in AutoCAD even when a 3d tool are used to make them. Or AutoCAD is used to do design work in 3D.  BIM exists but is just another data silo. A lot of the large engineering companies will try and push their own BIM solution which adds one more silo that no one else uses.<p>Everyone wants their own system and solution to be the single source of truth and that is a huge part of the problem.  On a project of thousands of people there is never going to be a single source of truth.  It&#x27;s like expecting a globally distributed system to be in sync.  Ultimately you have to chose between locking and eventual consistency and there is no other option.  Having a single BIM system helps but is not a silver bullet.  Because people will still get out of sync as other teams and tools are brought into play.</span>
              <div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
                  </font>
      </div></div></td></tr>
