                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="commtext c00">Not a software change but one reason you get asked a dozen times &quot;Are you having your the nails on your left big toe clipped&quot; (joke procedure in a hospital of course) is to help avoid exactly these errors.<p>Is the patient who you think it is.<p>Does the patient agree with what your procedure says to do.<p>Often the area to be worked on (like the left big toe in my joke) is marked and the patient agreed with that marking.<p>There are a number of other such safeguards, similar to pre-flight checklists in aviation.<p>Institution these processes have greatly reduced treatment errors.</span>
              <div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
                  </font>
