                  <span class="commtext c00">How to design thermally efficient buildings - especially everything that&#x27;s going on with climate crisis. The thermal comfort solution to everything in the last 70 years has been to put an HVAC on it, whereas if the buildings were designed properly, the need to actively maintain internal temperature is minimized.<p>After talking to architects, I&#x27;m dismayed that basic heat transfer is not a part of their curriculum.</span>
