                <tr class='athing comtr' id='32613098'><td><table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind' indent='2'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="80"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks">
      <center><a id='up_32613098'href='vote?id=32613098&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D32611247'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center>    </td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=whiteboardr" class="hnuser">whiteboardr</a> <span class="age" title="2022-08-26T21:45:20"><a href="item?id=32613098">42 days ago</a></span> <span id="unv_32613098"></span>          <span class='navs'>
             | <a href="#32611527" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">root</a> | <a href="#32612380" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">parent</a> | <a href="#32616328" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">next</a> <a class="togg clicky" id="32613098" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)">[–]</a><span class="onstory"></span>          </span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="commtext c00">There’s process and digital tools on the one end and on the other the ugly truth that almost everyone building spaces - be it commercial or residential - will be fed up with the low wages they get for the treciourous work they have to do in most cases since the number of people in “western countries” willing to work in construction is rapidly falling.</span>
